<section class="about-page">

  <div class="about-hero">
    <img src="/img/runnr_logo.png" alt="Runnr Logo" class="about-logo" />
    <h1 class="main-title">About Runnr</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="about-content">

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2 class="sub-title">What is Runnr?</h2>
      <p>
        Runnr is a community-powered fitness platform designed to help you stay 
        motivated, track your progress, and achieve your personal running goals.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Features</h2>
      <ul class="about-list">
        <li><strong>Track Your Runs:</strong> Record your distance, pace, and progress over time.</li>
        <li><strong>Join Community Goals:</strong> Set goals together with other users and stay accountable.</li>
        <li><strong>Follow Other Runners:</strong> Share your journey and cheer each other on.</li>
        <li><strong>Activity Feed:</strong> See what your friends and the community are achieving in real-time.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Why We Built Runnr</h2>
      <p>
        Staying consistent with fitness is hard — but it becomes easier with 
        community. Runnr was built to make running more social, inspiring, and fun. 
        Whether you're training for your first 5K or working toward a marathon, 
        Runnr helps you stay engaged and motivated every step of the way.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Get Started</h2>
      <% if (!loggedUser) { %>
        <p>
          Ready to start your journey? Create an account and join thousands of other
          runners working toward their goals.
        </p>
        <a href="/auth" class="btn submit-btn">Create Account</a>
      <% } else { %>
        <p>
          You’re already part of the community — keep exploring goals, following 
          runners, and tracking your progress.
        </p>
        <a href="/" class="btn submit-btn">Go to Dashboard</a>
      <% } %>
    </section>

  </div>

</section>
